author: Carter Kent
text:
Practice remembering as much from your recent timeline as possible and build on the days. Taking photos and videos along the way helps strengthen your memory muscle.

You can also practice memorizing one card from a deck of cards a day and repeating the sequence as it builds.

author: Carter Kent
text: Recall as many details from today at the end of the day as you can. If it gets difficult don't squeeze your brain. Breathe and say something like, "I'll allow it to come to me when it does," and your brain's computer fan will have a chance to cool down and hand you those details.
